        },
        {
          "title": "Design to scale out",
          "url": "https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2251007"
        }
      ],
      "labels": []
    },
    "Queue.0003": {
      "id": "Queue.0003",
      "description": "Managed Instance on App Service can install MSMQ client features via install scripts, but for queueing use Azure Service Bus/Queue Storage. If you require an MSMQ server, deploy on Azure VM and connect privately.\n\nYou are using MSMQ that is not currently supported in Azure App and containerized app. You can use Azure Queue Storage or Service Bus queues instead of MSMQ. Another option is to run MSMQ in Azure Virtual Machines.",
